net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor

Annotation Type Editor


  • public @interface Editor
    Editor metadata. You can use this to annotate a class as editable with an ValueEditor. This can be used instead of having a class implement ValueEditable.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.Class<? extends ValueEditor<?>> value
      The value editor class to use.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String validType
      The data type that the editor is considered valid for.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends ValueEditor<?>> value
        The value editor class to use.
        Returns:
        the class.

      • validType

        public abstract java.lang.String validType
        The data type that the editor is considered valid for. If not specified or an empty string, the editor is considered valid for all types.
        Returns:
        the type to consider as a valid type.
        Default:
        ""
